The paper deals with traffic analysis attacks, which are commonly studied in the computer security (cs.CR) and networking (cs.NI) communities. The attack described in the paper exploits a queuing side channel in routers, which falls under the category of network measurements (cs.NI) and network privacy (cs.CY). The paper also discusses website fingerprinting, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the privacy implications of the attack, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
